@timmytychilders 
⁣
Yesterday was my 6th anniversary of moving to NY! Yeah, I cried. Yeah, I partied. ⁣
⁣
There was no better way to celebrate than to celebrate both of my homes: seeing Tyler Childers at @radiocitymusichall ♥️ We used to go to his shows in Huntington, and now I get to go to his shows in NY and sing along with 6,018 people.
⁣
I grew up in a small town across the bridge in Ohio, with my church and friends and fun in Huntington. I moved to WV and graduated high school, and then moved and went to college, worked, and became who I am there. I wouldn’t be where I am without where I’m from. Cheers, NY 🥂

Shoutout to the cutie patootie hilarious performers from Philly who came to celebrate at @slipperroomny , @liveartbyadriano for my favorite accessory, and @angiepontani for this dream of a dress! I was doing my hot dog act at @missfrankieeleanor ‘s Burlesque Bingo bonanza and remembered sharing is caring: I went up to this gentleman and fed him my hot dog. As I shimmied my fringe-covered thong and squirted my condiments onto the rest of the hot dog, a little ketchup went rogue and got on his shirt. I leaned over and told him I had a Tide pen before running back to my pool and finishing my act.⁣
⁣
I came up to him right after I finished to tell him I would be back with my pen. Before I could speak, he put his hand out and politely asked for the pen. I looked at him, still in my pasties and thong, gestured to my nearly naked body, and asked where would I keep a Tide pen dressed like this, and I told him it’s not THAT kind of show. He laughed, I got the pen, cleaned him up, and sent him away with a hug 🌭💕⁣ Thank you for coming and for this video, @blaircooper_  or @_fit2dzl_ , I gotta admit I forgot in the condiment chaos and my friend getting so much of this silly show!
